	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />No, you always have to turn it off before you mess with the address.<br /><br />What I meant is that there's not enough time to turn it off and back on in an hblank, so rendering has to be <em>visibly</em> off if you're updating more than one palette entry (and really even for Indiana Jones' case of just the background colour, rendering is still off for a visible part of the scanline, it's just cleverly concealed).<br /><br />So, by &quot;rendering off&quot; I meant for multiple scanlines while you do your palette changes.

		

